Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Trim and halve @Persian cucumber{1}(trimmed and halved lengthwise); thinly slice crosswise into half-moons. Zest and quarter @lime{1}(zested and quartered). Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

== Ginger Rice ==

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the ginger and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Meatballs ==

While rice cooks, in a #large bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%ounce}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @ponzu sauce{6%milliliters}, garlic, remaining ginger, @salt{3/4%tsp}, and @pepper{}.

Form mixture into 10-12 meatballs. Place meatballs on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and cooked through, ~{14-16%minutes}.

== Pickled Veggie Salad ==

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, combine cucumber, @shredded carrots{4%ounce}, half the cilantro, and as much lime juice and lime zest as you like. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lime juice, and up to half the @sriracha{1%teaspoon} to taste (save the rest for the next step).

== Glaze and Assembly ==

In a second large bowl, combine @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon} with remaining sriracha to taste.

Once meatballs are done, carefully transfer to bowl with sauce; toss until meatballs are thoroughly coated and sauce is just warmed through.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{} and top with meatballs, any remaining sauce from bowl, and pickled veggie salad. Drizzle with sriracha lime mayo.

Garnish with remaining cilantro and serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.